`PPay``nPal` `CCredit Scoring`

`b---- Did you mean: paypal.score ----`

You can access your personal `PPay``nPal` report by running paypal.score.
This will show you your current score and the elements that make up your report.

`b----         API  Usage         ----`

In order to request the report of another user, you must have a valid `Napi_key`.

You can request an `Napi_key` for use with a single script: 
paypal.report { request: { script: "script.name", use_case: "reason for request" } }

After your request is `Lapproved`, you'll be issued with an `Napi_key` which can be
passed to this script to retrieve the caller's report.

For more detailed API information, use paypal.report { help: "" }.
